I'm cleaning the suite.

21
00:02:59,635 --> 00:03:00,719
You can't...

22
00:03:27,329 --> 00:03:28,997
You're gonna burn a hole
through my face.

23
00:03:30,541 --> 00:03:34,002
I know I'm a charming
and good-looking guy, but...

24
00:03:46,098 --> 00:03:47,182
What are you doing?

25
00:03:47,516 --> 00:03:48,684
Checking to see if you're real.

26
00:03:50,853 --> 00:03:53,856
How did you manage to show up
right at that moment?

27
00:03:57,067 --> 00:03:58,068
Unbelievable.

28
00:03:59,361 --> 00:04:00,529
What kind of moment was it?

29
00:04:00,863 --> 00:04:02,823
It was the moment I thought
that I wanted to see you.

30
00:04:07,411 --> 00:04:09,204
How could you say something
so heart-fluttering

31
00:04:10,789 --> 00:04:12,249
with such a straight face?

32
00:04:17,921 --> 00:04:19,047
I was regretting

33
00:04:19,923 --> 00:04:21,508
not being true to my feelings.

34
00:04:23,427 --> 00:04:25,179
I wanted to turn things back

35
00:04:25,804 --> 00:04:26,847
but thought it was too late.

36
00:04:27,473 --> 00:04:29,141
I was upset,
and it left me with regrets.

37
00:04:30,058 --> 00:04:31,268
But at the same time, I thought

38
00:04:32,102 --> 00:04:34,438
"Oh, I'd love to see
Ki-jun right now."

39
00:04:34,938 --> 00:04:37,399
Just when I was thinking that,
you appeared out of nowhere.

40
00:04:38,650 --> 00:04:40,194
I kind of knew that feeling

41
00:04:41,028 --> 00:04:43,238
so I rushed here
without wasting a second.

42
00:04:48,827 --> 00:04:50,913
Thank you for coming to get me.

43
00:04:57,002 --> 00:04:59,755
Let's turn things back one by one.

44
00:05:00,589 --> 00:05:01,715
I won't go to the US.

45
00:05:02,174 --> 00:05:03,509
I'm doing whatever it takes to stay.

46
00:05:04,009 --> 00:05:05,427
If you try to force me to go

47
00:05:05,928 --> 00:05:07,846
I'll lie down flat in the lobby
to protest so I can stay.

48
00:05:11,308 --> 00:05:15,813
The thing is, going to the US office
would be a great opportunity for you.

49
00:05:16,522 --> 00:05:18,148
Didn't we agree to be honest?

50
00:05:20,609 --> 00:05:21,944
Should I actually go?

51
00:05:24,446 --> 00:05:26,281
No, don't go.

52
00:05:26,573 --> 00:05:27,783
Stay right next to me.

53
00:05:29,493 --> 00:05:30,536
You bet.

54
00:05:50,806 --> 00:05:53,267
- That's it?
- Yes, that's it.

55
00:05:55,018 --> 00:05:56,103
What about the other side?

56
00:06:37,853 --> 00:06:40,522
What's this?
We only just said goodbye.

57
00:06:40,856 --> 00:06:41,857
Do you miss me already?

58
00:06:42,566 --> 00:06:44,610
Yes, I miss you.

59
00:06:47,863 --> 00:06:49,239
My heart almost burst.

60
00:06:49,531 --> 00:06:50,699
Over that?

61
00:06:51,575 --> 00:06:53,452
You should brace yourself.

62
00:06:54,077 --> 00:06:55,746
Once I start dating someone

63
00:06:55,829 --> 00:06:57,539
I get all passionate and fired up.

64
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:00,542
I knew it.

65
00:07:01,084 --> 00:07:03,420
I should brace myself
to date someone like you.

66
00:07:05,213 --> 00:07:06,673
I'm not so easygoing either.

67
00:07:07,049 --> 00:07:09,635
So you should brace yourself as well.

68
00:07:09,801 --> 00:07:10,886
What, really?

69
00:07:11,720 --> 00:07:13,263
What should I prepare first?

70
00:07:16,016 --> 00:07:18,185
Why don't we figure out
what to call each other?

71
00:07:18,810 --> 00:07:20,938
I don't want
to have to call you "Ms. Joo."

72
00:07:21,021 --> 00:07:22,356
It's too formal and unfriendly.

73
00:07:24,524 --> 00:07:25,525
My darling In-a.

74
00:07:26,985 --> 00:07:27,986
In-a.

75
00:07:29,071 --> 00:07:30,656
Now that I think about it

76
00:07:31,073 --> 00:07:32,532
you have a beautiful name.

77
00:07:33,825 --> 00:07:34,868
Joo In-a.

78
00:07:37,412 --> 00:07:39,414
- Hi, guys.
- Hey.

79
00:07:43,126 --> 00:07:44,836
- Let's drink.
- Cheers.

80
00:07:49,967 --> 00:07:52,177
Jae-yeol, what's up with you?

81
00:07:52,260 --> 00:07:53,845
You never joined us
when we invited you before.

82
00:07:55,263 --> 00:07:56,598
I know I was too distant.

83
00:07:57,516 --> 00:07:58,725
Sorry about that.

84
00:07:59,810 --> 00:08:02,854
Hey, I think you should slow down.

85
00:08:02,938 --> 00:08:04,064
Aren't you drinking too much?

86
00:08:05,399 --> 00:08:09,152
Are you getting wasted because
your stepbrother was made co-VP?

87
00:08:09,319 --> 00:08:10,445
I read about that in the news.

88
00:08:10,779 --> 00:08:12,197
Your father's just...

89
00:08:12,781 --> 00:08:16,159
He could've just put things in order
instead of making him co-VP.

90
00:08:16,243 --> 00:08:18,036
It's like he put you two
in a cage to fight.

91
00:08:18,370 --> 00:08:20,747
You talk too much
when we're here to drink.

92
00:08:21,289 --> 00:08:22,916
- Drink up.
- Yes.

93
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:25,293
Jae-yeol rarely joins us for drinks.

94
00:08:25,544 --> 00:08:27,796
- Let's drink.
- And get wasted.

95
00:09:21,516 --> 00:09:22,517
It's cold, isn't it?

96
00:09:23,518 --> 00:09:24,519
No.

97
00:09:29,858 --> 00:09:31,234
Do you like it that much?

98
00:09:32,152 --> 00:09:33,153
Yes.

99
00:09:35,989 --> 00:09:38,658
I can't believe I look forward
to going to work in the morning.

100
00:09:39,326 --> 00:09:40,327
For real?

101
00:09:40,827 --> 00:09:42,412
I love heading into work.

102
00:09:42,621 --> 00:09:44,790
Work is much more fun
than being bored at home.

103
00:09:45,290 --> 00:09:46,291
No wonder.

104
00:09:47,417 --> 00:09:49,044
You had a look of madness
in your eyes.

105
00:09:52,047 --> 00:09:55,967
We'll do more fun things together
other than just work.

106
00:09:56,802 --> 00:09:58,929
Clear your schedule this weekend.

107
00:09:59,846 --> 00:10:04,101
We went all the way to Jeju Island
but had to return right away.

108
00:10:04,851 --> 00:10:06,436
I booked a pool villa in Sokcho.

109
00:10:07,145 --> 00:10:09,773
Let's take our time
to play in the sea

110
00:10:10,232 --> 00:10:11,316
and get some fresh air.

111
00:10:12,901 --> 00:10:14,778
Is this an overnight trip?

112
00:10:19,574 --> 00:10:21,576
It's... Well...

113
00:10:21,868 --> 00:10:24,037
A one-day trip
won't leave us much time.

114
00:10:29,876 --> 00:10:30,961
I love it.

115
00:10:36,049 --> 00:10:37,759
I'm kind of worried

116
00:10:38,593 --> 00:10:41,012
that I won't be able to hide
how much I like you at work.

117
00:10:41,388 --> 00:10:43,473
- What should I do?
- I'd love to see that.

118
00:10:44,266 --> 00:10:45,267
Not being able to hide it.

119
00:10:47,894 --> 00:10:49,187
Don't smile like that.

120
00:10:49,396 --> 00:10:51,565
If you smile, I can't help but smile,
and my feelings will show.

121
00:10:54,943 --> 00:10:57,946
This is a serious matter.
It's going to be too obvious.

122
00:10:59,072 --> 00:11:00,657
Too obvious, my foot.

123
00:11:12,752 --> 00:11:14,087
Even when she's in a relationship

124
00:11:15,714 --> 00:11:19,134
Joo In-a was
still her old self at work.

125
00:11:20,135 --> 00:11:22,387
So what is your conclusion?

126
00:11:23,054 --> 00:11:25,348
It doesn't say on this page
or on this page.

127
00:11:26,558 --> 00:11:28,768
There's nothing.
This report has no key point!

128
00:11:29,728 --> 00:11:30,729
See this?

129
00:11:31,479 --> 00:11:33,565
Do you see a key point
in this report?

130
00:11:35,609 --> 00:11:39,154
This is the kind of report you should
pay to write, not be paid to write.

131
00:11:39,446 --> 00:11:40,488
It's a waste of paper.

132
00:11:41,615 --> 00:11:42,824
Rewrite the whole thing.

133
00:12:06,890 --> 00:12:08,266
Are you all right, Mr. Noh?

134
00:12:09,684 --> 00:12:10,685
Mr. Noh.

135
00:12:11,019 --> 00:12:12,854
Did you do something
to get on her nerves?

136
00:12:13,480 --> 00:12:16,024
No, it's because he's working
too much.

137
00:12:16,691 --> 00:12:18,777
Mr. Noh, be more like me.

138
00:12:19,778 --> 00:12:21,404
Talk more and do less.

139
00:12:21,488 --> 00:12:24,157
The more an auditor does,
the harder they get audited.

140
00:12:24,366 --> 00:12:26,368
The more you do,
the more there is to criticize.

141
00:12:28,119 --> 00:12:30,038
Those are such wise words.

142
00:12:30,580 --> 00:12:32,290
For someone who doesn't do much

143
00:12:32,374 --> 00:12:36,628
