overtime pay each month?

144
00:12:36,711 --> 00:12:38,463
Will you all stop it?

145
00:12:38,922 --> 00:12:39,923
Ms. Yoon.

146
00:12:40,340 --> 00:12:42,634
Did you finish the slides
for the presentation on our clubs?

147
00:12:42,717 --> 00:12:45,136
Yes, I emailed you the final version.

148
00:12:45,220 --> 00:12:46,429
Good job.

149
00:12:46,680 --> 00:12:50,350
Did you add as many photos, tables,
and animations as possible?

150
00:12:52,060 --> 00:12:53,812
I'm sure you did your job.

151
00:12:53,895 --> 00:12:54,896
Good for you.

152
00:12:55,230 --> 00:12:58,233
When we present the report
to Ms. Joo later

153
00:12:58,316 --> 00:12:59,693
you're all coming with me.

154
00:13:00,694 --> 00:13:01,736
You, too, Mr. Noh.

155
00:13:02,654 --> 00:13:05,323
Ms. Joo is a really nice person.

156
00:13:05,407 --> 00:13:06,700
Don't be too afraid of her.

157
00:13:07,534 --> 00:13:08,576
Okay.

158
00:13:09,911 --> 00:13:11,496
I'm sure she's a nice person.

159
00:13:18,003 --> 00:13:19,337
The problem is that she's too nice.

160
00:13:39,065 --> 00:13:40,066
Ms. Park?

161
00:13:41,735 --> 00:13:45,363
- Yes?
- When will VP Jeon be here?

162
00:13:46,197 --> 00:13:48,783
He isn't well today.

163
00:13:50,118 --> 00:13:52,620
I'll present the agenda instead.

164
00:13:56,833 --> 00:13:57,834
Okay.

165
00:13:58,585 --> 00:14:00,712
We can't wait forever.

166
00:14:08,595 --> 00:14:09,763
Let's start without him.

167
00:14:10,472 --> 00:14:13,350
Don't you forget
that I am a VP as well.

168
00:14:14,184 --> 00:14:16,811
Yes, I think
it would be fine to start.

169
00:14:17,520 --> 00:14:19,272
Ms. Park, you can leave.

170
00:14:19,356 --> 00:14:20,815
- But...
- Being a secretary

171
00:14:21,149 --> 00:14:24,152
doesn't give you the right
to attend in a VP's place.

172
00:14:41,419 --> 00:14:44,339
VICE PRESIDENT

173
00:14:47,550 --> 00:14:49,761
SECRETARY PARK A-JEONG

174
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:48,486
- Gosh, the water...
- It's so clear.

175
00:15:49,571 --> 00:15:51,656
Were they rockfish? Did you see them?

176
00:15:51,739 --> 00:15:52,866
- Yes.
- There was a swarm.

177
00:15:52,949 --> 00:15:55,034
- It was amazing.
- Just fantastic.

178
00:15:55,618 --> 00:15:56,744
- Did you notice?
- Yes.

179
00:15:56,828 --> 00:15:58,121
- Right?
- Did you?

180
00:15:58,204 --> 00:15:59,497
- I saw.
- What was that?

181
00:16:00,331 --> 00:16:01,499
It was incredible.

182
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:03,251
The water's so clear today.

183
00:16:03,543 --> 00:16:05,253
- It's a rare occasion.
- I know.

184
00:16:11,593 --> 00:16:12,969
- You're back.
- Yes.

185
00:16:13,386 --> 00:16:14,429
Did you have fun?

186
00:16:15,096 --> 00:16:16,347
Is Seo-yeon in bed?

187
00:16:16,639 --> 00:16:17,640
Yes.

188
00:16:18,808 --> 00:16:21,853
Her English kindergarten is hosting
a cooking class on the 29th.

189
00:16:21,936 --> 00:16:23,062
You can make it, right?

190
00:16:28,276 --> 00:16:30,278
- I have a club meeting on the 29th.
- Again?

191
00:16:30,737 --> 00:16:33,072
Why do you have to go
scuba diving that often?

192
00:16:35,992 --> 00:16:37,744
Can't you miss it for once?

193
00:16:38,286 --> 00:16:40,914
I went on my own
to Seo-yeon's speech contest.

194
00:16:40,997 --> 00:16:42,749
Do you know how upset she was
that you'd missed it?

195
00:16:42,832 --> 00:16:45,293
I'll be at the next one.

196
00:16:47,295 --> 00:16:49,088
Are you sure you go scuba diving?

197
00:16:49,797 --> 00:16:51,216
Are you up to something else?

198
00:17:08,525 --> 00:17:09,567
AUDIT SUMMARY

199
00:17:10,026 --> 00:17:14,531
We found four cases in which
clubs fraudulently enrolled

200
00:17:14,614 --> 00:17:18,159
new recruits or temporary staff
to collect extra club funds.

201
00:17:18,243 --> 00:17:21,746
And in seven cases,
club admin embezzled club funds

202
00:17:21,829 --> 00:17:24,582
rented spaces or paid instructors
for personal gain.

203
00:17:26,042 --> 00:17:28,336
We found eight malpractice cases
where club members

204
00:17:28,419 --> 00:17:31,005
hired businesses
run by friends or family.

205
00:17:31,089 --> 00:17:34,467
In two cases, there were issues
that constituted gambling.

206
00:17:36,511 --> 00:17:38,972
The in-house clubs currently hand in

207
00:17:39,055 --> 00:17:41,933
- an activity report yearly, right?
- Yes, that's right.

208
00:17:42,016 --> 00:17:45,770
Have them submit one each quarter
with more details in the report.

209
00:17:45,853 --> 00:17:47,146
Ask HR to make the announcement.

210
00:17:47,230 --> 00:17:48,856
Okay, I'll relay the message.

211
00:17:48,940 --> 00:17:52,026
We also have a club-related PM case.

212
00:17:53,903 --> 00:17:56,948
The wife of Min Tae-woo
at Haemu International contacted us.

213
00:17:57,031 --> 00:18:00,118
Her husband is way too active
in the scuba diving club.

214
00:18:00,201 --> 00:18:02,412
She's not entirely sure
their activities are wholesome.

215
00:18:02,495 --> 00:18:06,708
It's hard to tell because of the gear
but the man on the right is Mr. Min.

216
00:18:06,791 --> 00:18:09,919
The person on the right is
suspected to be his affair partner.

217
00:18:10,003 --> 00:18:12,672
The wife found many photos
of this person in particular.

218
00:18:12,755 --> 00:18:14,507
Aren't they just enjoying a hobby?

219
00:18:14,591 --> 00:18:16,301
It did seem somewhat odd.

220
00:18:16,384 --> 00:18:19,012
Mr. Min supposedly dislikes water
and didn't even swim.

221
00:18:19,095 --> 00:18:22,015
He goes scuba diving
almost every week now.

222
00:18:22,098 --> 00:18:24,475
He's known to even
take time off work to go.

223
00:18:24,559 --> 00:18:26,811
And at home,
he always says he's tired.

224
00:18:26,894 --> 00:18:29,606
Oh, and he gets calls at dawn
or in the middle of the night

225
00:18:29,689 --> 00:18:31,357
and jumps up to go out.

226
00:18:31,441 --> 00:18:34,444
Many complain
that company clubs foster affairs

227
00:18:34,527 --> 00:18:37,989
and that the company encourages it
by covering expenses.

228
00:18:38,072 --> 00:18:41,075
Why don't we make this an example
and look into this incident?

229
00:18:41,159 --> 00:18:44,037
We won't get anywhere
with what we have if they deny it.

230
00:18:46,289 --> 00:18:49,500
Let's attend a club outing
and see how things actually are.

231
00:18:51,169 --> 00:18:52,295
Mr. Noh.

232
00:18:52,712 --> 00:18:54,088
Do you know how to scuba-dive?

233
00:18:55,632 --> 00:18:58,009
I did take a few lessons
on a trip once.

234
00:18:58,092 --> 00:18:59,969
You should go to Mr. Min's club

235
00:19:00,053 --> 00:19:01,137
- this weekend.
- What?

236
00:19:04,766 --> 00:19:06,517
This weekend

237
00:19:07,935 --> 00:19:10,438
I have an important appointment.

238
00:19:12,482 --> 00:19:13,483
Do you?

239
00:19:14,442 --> 00:19:17,070
Is anyone else able to scuba-dive?

240
00:19:17,654 --> 00:19:19,781
Extended exposure to water
gives me a rash.

241
00:19:19,864 --> 00:19:21,115
- The sea...
- That's bad.

242
00:19:21,199 --> 00:19:23,534
I almost drowned in a river
as a child and the trauma...

243
00:19:23,618 --> 00:19:25,536
- I can't equalize underwater.
- I can't manage.

244
00:19:25,620 --> 00:19:27,330
I refuse to work on weekends.

245
00:19:27,413 --> 00:19:29,290
It verges on a rare disease.

246
00:19:29,999 --> 00:19:31,334
Oh, dear...

247
00:19:32,043 --> 00:19:33,544
I'm left with no choice, then.

248
00:19:34,295 --> 00:19:35,797
I love scuba diving.

249
00:19:37,006 --> 00:19:38,549
- I'll go.
- What?

250
00:19:38,633 --> 00:19:39,676
What?

251
00:19:45,973 --> 00:19:47,767
Don't you have anything planned

252
00:19:48,476 --> 00:19:50,395
for this weekend?

253
00:19:50,478 --> 00:19:52,855
I don't have
any special plans this weekend.

254
00:19:53,523 --> 00:19:55,149
Clear your schedule this weekend.

255
00:19:55,233 --> 00:19:56,901
I booked a pool villa in Sokcho.

256
00:19:56,984 --> 00:19:58,528
I thought I didn't have plans.

257
00:20:02,573 --> 00:20:03,991
You do have plans, then.

258
00:20:04,826 --> 00:20:06,452
How could you?

259
00:20:07,537 --> 00:20:10,748
Aren't you happy
we get to travel together?

260
00:20:11,374 --> 00:20:13,793
We're doing
exactly what we planned to do.

261
00:20:13,876 --> 00:20:15,211
We see the sea
and get some fresh air.

262
00:20:15,294 --> 00:20:16,838
- Plus, we get to work, too.
- Goodness.

263
00:20:16,921 --> 00:20:18,089
We hit two birds with one stone

264
00:20:18,172 --> 00:20:20,133
by going swimming
and seeing some fish.

265
00:20:20,216 --> 00:20:23,469
You said you get passionate
when you start dating.

266
00:20:23,553 --> 00:20:25,304
But all you did was
make me work passionately.

267
00:20:25,388 --> 00:20:27,890
I thought I was going
to burn to ashes with your passion.

268
00:20:27,974 --> 00:20:30,059
That was because we had a lot to do

269
00:20:30,143 --> 00:20:31,769
because of the previous week's trip.

270
00:20:31,853 --> 00:20:34,689
Also, I didn't want anyone at work
to notice anything.

271
00:20:34,897 --> 00:20:36,232
I put on an act with a poker face.

272
00:20:36,315 --> 00:20:38,985
You got so into that act
that you forgot our weekend plan.

273
00:20:40,987 --> 00:20:43,823
That was because it's been so long
since I made weekend plans.

274
00:20:44,490 --> 00:20:45,742
Plus, this is work.

275
00:20:45,825 --> 00:20:48,077
I'm very good at separating
work from my personal life.

276
00:20:48,161 --> 00:20:50,037
Yes, of course. I get it, Ms. Joo.

277
00:20:50,455 --> 00:20:52,874
We're on a business trip,
not a pleasure cruise.

278
00:20:52,957 --> 00:20:55,752
I'll make sure to act accordingly,
completely aloof and official.

279
00:20:59,005 --> 00:21:00,631
Ki-jun, are you actually angry?

280
00:21:01,507 --> 00:21:02,550
Yes.

281
00:21:04,177 --> 00:21:06,429
You fool. You twit.

282
00:21:06,679 --> 00:21:08,973
How could you forget your first date?

283
00:21:09,265 --> 00:21:11,017
- Get a grip, In-a!
- Don't.

284
00:21:11,100 --> 00:21:12,602
- What are you doing?
- What?

285
00:21:12,685 --> 00:21:13,895
I deserve a good scolding.

286
00:21:13,978 --> 00:21:17,440
- You fool. You twit. You moron.
- No, stop it. Don't do that.

287
00:21:17,523 --> 00:21:19,484
I was kidding, okay?

288
00:21:19,776 --> 00:21:21,611
I'm not angry at all. I was joking.

289
00:21:21,694 --> 00:21:23,988
- You seemed really angry.
- I wasn't.

290
00:21:24,071 --> 00:21:25,573
I wasn't even sulking.

291
00:21:26,157 --> 00:21:27,658
I'm really sorry.

292
00:21:28,117 --> 00:21:29,243
Don't be.

293
00:21:30,036 --> 00:21:31,579
Goodness...

294
00:21:37,168 --> 00:21:40,296
We have new members joining us today.

295
00:21:40,463 --> 00:21:43,424
It's Ms. Joo In-a, Head of Audit
from the head office

296
00:21:43,508 --> 00:21:45,927
and Assistant Manager Noh Ki-jun.

297
00:21:46,677 --> 00:21:49,096
- It's a pleasure to meet you all.
- Applause.

298
00:21:49,847 --> 00:21:51,933
You're both from the Audit Team

299
00:21:52,016 --> 00:21:53,810
so I feel somewhat nervous.

300
00:21:53,893 --> 00:21:58,064
We use our funds appropriately
and we do nothing wrong, do we?

301
00:21:58,147 --> 00:21:59,607
- Do you all agree?
- Yes.

302
00:21:59,690 --> 00:22:02,360
Club president, don't you know
saying that makes you look guilty?

303
00:22:03,110 --> 00:22:04,320
You have a point.

304
00:22:04,403 --> 00:22:07,949
We have a small group today,
so we'll go out together.

305
00:22:08,032 --> 00:22:09,951
Check your equipment thoroughly.

306
00:22:10,034 --> 00:22:11,202
- Okay.
- Okay.

307
00:22:11,410 --> 00:22:12,537
Get to it.

308
00:22:18,209 --> 00:22:19,418
Hey.

309
00:22:36,018 --> 00:22:37,103
Watch out.

310
00:22:37,186 --> 00:22:39,605
This valve here needs to be checked.

311
00:22:40,523 --> 00:22:42,191
We run on a buddy system.

312
00:22:42,275 --> 00:22:43,818
This is your first dive with us

313
00:22:43,901 --> 00:22:46,195
so you should partner
with someone more experienced.

314
00:22:46,445 --> 00:22:49,407
I will partner with Mr. Min, then.

315
00:22:49,574 --> 00:22:52,702
The way he's helping her
looks reliable and reassuring.

316
00:22:52,785 --> 00:22:55,663
Then Mr. Min, you'll go out with him.

317
00:22:55,746 --> 00:22:57,498
- Okay.
- Ms. Joo, your partner...

318
00:22:57,582 --> 00:22:58,749
I volunteer.

319
00:23:22,231 --> 00:23:24,233
Mr. Min and Ms. Ha seem pretty close.

320
00:23:24,859 --> 00:23:26,360
Yes, they do.

321
00:23:28,571 --> 00:23:30,948
Are you upset Ms. Ha
is his possible fling?

322
00:23:31,407 --> 00:23:32,450
What?

323
00:23:33,117 --> 00:23:36,579
You couldn't seem to take
your eyes off her.

324
00:23:36,662 --> 00:23:39,624
What does that mean work-wise?

325
00:23:40,625 --> 00:23:43,628
My eyes were not locked onto her.

326
00:23:44,754 --> 00:23:46,297
It's all work-related.

327
00:23:46,672 --> 00:23:50,843
I just wanted to confirm if she was
the other person in the photos.

328
00:23:51,969 --> 00:23:52,970
I'll see you later.

329
00:23:55,306 --> 00:23:56,432
Personal-wise.

330
00:24:00,519 --> 00:24:01,646
Gosh...

331
00:24:02,146 --> 00:24:04,649
Get ready to dive.
Get your equipment.

332
00:24:04,732 --> 00:24:05,816
- Okay.
- Okay.

333
00:24:06,567 --> 00:24:07,735
Be sure to check that.

334
00:24:08,819 --> 00:24:10,321
- Okay, checked.
- Good.

335
00:24:10,821 --> 00:24:12,573
- It's all done.
- Great.

336
00:26:33,631 --> 00:26:35,257
Are you all right?

337
00:26:47,394 --> 00:26:49,313
That seemed like a panic attack.

338
00:26:50,439 --> 00:26:52,525
Are you claustrophobic or something?

339
00:26:53,150 --> 00:26:55,528
I'm fine. It wasn't anything serious.

340
00:26:55,611 --> 00:26:57,196
Did you tell the instructor?

341
00:26:57,655 --> 00:27:00,908
You should inform the others
for their safety, too.

342
00:27:00,991 --> 00:27:02,451
It's not that serious, okay?

343
00:27:04,495 --> 00:27:09,834
Are you afraid you won't get to dive
if the others find out about this?

344
00:27:10,334 --> 00:27:11,752
Do you love to dive that much?

345
00:27:11,836 --> 00:27:14,213
You say too much
for someone who just joined.

346
00:27:14,839 --> 00:27:16,340
I can handle my business.

347
00:27:17,675 --> 00:27:18,968
Stay out of it.

348
00:27:36,694 --> 00:27:37,862
Oh, come on.

349
00:27:38,112 --> 00:27:39,530
It was a great dive.

350
00:27:40,656 --> 00:27:44,869
He braves panic attacks to dive
just so he can see a woman regularly?

351
00:27:45,911 --> 00:27:48,247
He could if he likes her that much.

352
00:27:48,330 --> 00:27:50,833
It makes for a good excuse
for them to spend time together.

353
00:27:52,626 --> 00:27:54,753
Ms. Ha is a veteran diver.

354
00:27:55,629 --> 00:27:57,631
This story makes more sense.

355
00:27:57,715 --> 00:27:59,341
Mr. Min fell for Ms. Ha first

356
00:27:59,425 --> 00:28:01,802
found out what her hobby was,
and joined the club.

357
00:28:03,971 --> 00:28:06,223
Gosh, if that's true

358
00:28:07,474 --> 00:28:09,143
he's risking his life
for just an affair.

359
00:28:10,227 --> 00:28:12,897
I'm so sorry about this.
I'd love to join you for dinner

360
00:28:12,980 --> 00:28:15,566
but I have to get back to attend
an old coworker's father's funeral.

361
00:28:15,649 --> 00:28:17,860
I had a great time today.
See you on the next dive.

362
00:28:17,943 --> 00:28:19,195
- Goodbye.
- Get back safely.

363
00:28:19,278 --> 00:28:21,030
- Bye.
- Sleep well.

364
00:28:21,113 --> 00:28:22,198
- Bye.
- Goodbye.

365
00:28:22,698 --> 00:28:24,074
What do we eat for dinner?

366
00:28:24,158 --> 00:28:26,202
We had so much fun
swimming with the fish.

367
00:28:26,285 --> 00:28:28,245
We're not eating raw fish, are we?

368
00:28:29,246 --> 00:28:30,581
How about a toast?

369
00:28:30,998 --> 00:28:33,000
- Good dive!
- Good dive!

370
00:28:33,083 --> 00:28:34,835
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

371
00:28:41,592 --> 00:28:43,219
They were friends only moments ago.

372
00:28:44,762 --> 00:28:45,971
Goodbye, little fishies.

373
00:28:48,599 --> 00:28:51,352
Ms. Joo is hilarious.
Don't you think?

374
00:28:54,480 --> 00:28:57,942
These aren't the fish we saw,
so there's no need to feel bad.

375
00:28:58,317 --> 00:28:59,985
The ssamjang here is the best.

376
00:29:00,653 --> 00:29:02,154
Here we go. Open up.

377
00:29:07,576 --> 00:29:08,744
Is it good?

378
00:29:13,791 --> 00:29:15,334
Mr. Noh, you, too. Open up.

379
00:29:17,086 --> 00:29:19,129
- What?
- Don't be shy.

380
00:29:19,463 --> 00:29:20,798
Open your mouth wide.

381
00:29:30,766 --> 00:29:32,351
That tastes amazing.

382
00:29:32,977 --> 00:29:35,229
Ms. Ha, your wraps are the best.

383
00:29:35,312 --> 00:29:37,856
Who taught you the recipe?

384
00:29:38,732 --> 00:29:39,817
It's so good.

385
00:30:05,718 --> 00:30:07,928
He drank enough alcohol
to kill himself.

386
00:30:08,554 --> 00:30:09,763
If you were any later

387
00:30:10,806 --> 00:30:12,099
something terrible could've happened.

388
00:30:39,877 --> 00:30:41,086
That's not going to happen.

389
00:30:42,713 --> 00:30:44,381
We can't go back
to how things used to be.

390
00:30:47,384 --> 00:30:48,469
What I'm trying to say is

391
00:30:49,928 --> 00:30:52,056
I'm never going back to you,
Jae-yeol.

392
00:31:07,946 --> 00:31:09,990
OUR DEEPEST CONDOLENCES

393
00:31:10,074 --> 00:31:11,909
MAY HE REST IN PEACE

394
00:31:14,787 --> 00:31:17,039
Are you recruitment peers
with Mr. Lee, then?

395
00:31:17,122 --> 00:31:18,582
He's one of the few guys
from the same batch.

396
00:31:18,665 --> 00:31:20,918
Right. You realize
that when you're at work

397
00:31:21,001 --> 00:31:23,003
your recruitment peer is
the closest you have to a friend.

398
00:31:23,087 --> 00:31:24,797
All my peers retired early

399
00:31:24,880 --> 00:31:26,298
- and recently, one...
- Mr. Han.

400
00:31:26,382 --> 00:31:28,300
- Long time no see.
- Hi, take a seat.

401
00:31:28,384 --> 00:31:30,302
- Hello.
- Let me introduce him, Mr. Moo.

402
00:31:30,386 --> 00:31:33,263
This is Yoon Sang-ho from Haemu
International Global Business Team.

403
00:31:33,847 --> 00:31:35,599
This is Audit Team's Leader
Moo Kwang-il.

404
00:31:35,682 --> 00:31:37,017
- It's a pleasure.
- Same here.

405
00:31:37,101 --> 00:31:39,061
I met two others
from your team today.

406
00:31:39,144 --> 00:31:41,897
I just got back
from the Scuba Diving Club

407
00:31:41,980 --> 00:31:45,984
and your head Ms. Joo
and Mr. Noh were there.

408
00:31:46,068 --> 00:31:47,861
- Oh, I see.
- Yes.

409
00:31:47,945 --> 00:31:50,656
- Let me pour you one.
- No, I drove here.

410
00:31:50,739 --> 00:31:52,491
- I'll pour you one instead.
- What a pity.

411
00:31:52,574 --> 00:31:54,660
- Not at all.
- Didn't you drive here

412
00:31:54,743 --> 00:31:57,996
- if you just got back from a trip?
- I can always hire a driver.

413
00:31:58,080 --> 00:31:59,957
- It's an honor to meet you.
- Same here.

414
00:32:04,420 --> 00:32:06,004
What's up with Ms. Ha?

415
00:32:06,713 --> 00:32:08,674
She stuck close to Mr. Min

416
00:32:09,133 --> 00:32:11,343
but then
she seemed interested in you, too.

417
00:32:11,677 --> 00:32:16,473
Well, I'm usually at the center
of everyone's attention.

418
00:32:16,557 --> 00:32:19,351
Is she the type who wants to get
all the men's attention?

419
00:32:21,019 --> 00:32:23,856
It's not all men, but me.

420
00:32:24,690 --> 00:32:26,191
It's because I'm Noh Ki-jun.

421
00:32:27,985 --> 00:32:29,361
It's Min and Ha.

422
00:32:36,326 --> 00:32:40,873
He's loading her equipment
into his car, isn't he?

423
00:32:42,166 --> 00:32:43,792
Something's up with them.

424
00:32:54,219 --> 00:32:55,220
Wait.

425
00:32:56,096 --> 00:32:57,556
Is he driving off with the equipment?

426
00:32:58,765 --> 00:32:59,766
Yes.

427
00:32:59,850 --> 00:33:02,561
It looks like Mr. Min
got a call from someone.

428
00:33:05,230 --> 00:33:06,315
Where's Ms. Ha?

429
00:33:23,790 --> 00:33:25,501
I'm really sorry.

430
00:33:25,584 --> 00:33:28,086
I get carsick easily
and can't sit in the back.

431
00:33:28,921 --> 00:33:31,131
Plus, that's usually
where the boss sits, right?

432
00:33:31,757 --> 00:33:32,966
You're the boss.

433
00:33:33,759 --> 00:33:35,427
I appreciate that.

434
00:33:35,511 --> 00:33:36,845
By the way...

435
00:33:37,596 --> 00:33:39,598
Where do you live, Mr. Noh?

436
00:33:39,848 --> 00:33:41,975
- What?
- Do you live nearby?

437
00:33:43,018 --> 00:33:46,355
I hope you don't have to make
too long a detour.

438
00:33:46,438 --> 00:33:48,273
I don't. It's fine.

439
00:33:49,983 --> 00:33:51,026
I have a question.

440
00:33:53,612 --> 00:33:57,199
Don't you dislike joining a club
with your direct superior?

441
00:33:57,282 --> 00:33:58,784
Oh, gosh. I can hear every word.

442
00:33:59,660 --> 00:34:01,119
My bad.

443
00:34:02,287 --> 00:34:04,498
Our dear Mr. Min's having a hard time

444
00:34:04,581 --> 00:34:08,126
because his superior Mr. Yoon
is in the same club.

445
00:34:14,383 --> 00:34:17,970
You and Mr. Min must be really close.

446
00:34:18,679 --> 00:34:20,806
You talked so much earlier today

447
00:34:20,889 --> 00:34:23,809
and just now you called him
"our dear Mr. Min."

448
00:34:24,601 --> 00:34:25,644
Oh, gosh.

449
00:34:27,396 --> 00:34:28,730
You got the wrong idea.

450
00:34:30,148 --> 00:34:32,985
Mr. Min's married with a kid.

451
00:34:33,318 --> 00:34:34,861
We're second cousins.

452
00:34:35,571 --> 00:34:37,489
It's a pure coincidence
that we joined the same club.

453
00:34:38,323 --> 00:34:40,617
Then you and Mr. Min

454
00:34:41,159 --> 00:34:42,744
are just relatives?

455
00:34:43,078 --> 00:34:46,623
Yes, that's why I loaded
my equipment in his trunk.

456
00:34:47,666 --> 00:34:50,002
Wait, what? Are you serious?

457
00:34:50,335 --> 00:34:52,004
Where did you get that idea?

458
00:34:52,963 --> 00:34:56,466
Hey, you must
be working out, Mr. Noh.

459
00:34:56,550 --> 00:34:58,760
Gosh, that's just hilarious.

460
00:34:58,844 --> 00:35:00,887
I almost got the wrong idea
about you two.

461
00:35:00,971 --> 00:35:03,807
It's so funny how things may seem.

462
00:35:03,890 --> 00:35:05,183
Goodness...

463
00:35:10,856 --> 00:35:13,483
So in the end, that new recruit

464
00:35:13,567 --> 00:35:16,653
raided HR and made a huge fuss,
which resulted in

465
00:35:16,737 --> 00:35:19,948
kicking out Mr. Lee
to another branch.

466
00:35:20,032 --> 00:35:23,118
These days,
people call everything gaslighting.

467
00:35:23,201 --> 00:35:24,620
We can't even talk anymore.

468
00:35:24,703 --> 00:35:26,663
These kids only learned
the worst in everything.

469
00:35:26,747 --> 00:35:28,832
I'm sure there was a situation...

470
00:35:28,915 --> 00:35:30,834
It doesn't matter
what the situation is.

471
00:35:30,917 --> 00:35:34,004
How dare some rookie dare
to kick the department head out?

472
00:35:34,087 --> 00:35:35,422
How can this happen?

473
00:35:35,672 --> 00:35:38,634
Mr. Moo, if this happened in the army

474
00:35:38,717 --> 00:35:42,429
it'd be like a private messing
with the division commander. Jeez.

475
00:35:42,512 --> 00:35:44,973
Well, the office
isn't the same as the army.

476
00:35:45,223 --> 00:35:47,059
I mean, are they any different?

477
00:35:47,142 --> 00:35:48,977
They're both organizations,
and there are ranks.

478
00:35:49,061 --> 00:35:52,397
If so, we must also establish
proper discipline.

479
00:35:52,481 --> 00:35:54,775
That's what I'm trying to say.

480
00:35:54,858 --> 00:35:58,987
I thought you'd be more open-minded
because you're called the Global Team

481
00:35:59,071 --> 00:36:01,406
but you're even more old-fashioned
than a Korean Audit Team.

482
00:36:01,823 --> 00:36:03,283
Well, old-fashioned?

483
00:36:03,367 --> 00:36:05,994
When we have team dinners,
we don't even drink regular soju.

484
00:36:06,078 --> 00:36:08,747
We only get the red caps,
the ones with more alcohol content.

485
00:36:09,831 --> 00:36:11,041
Goodness, look at the time.

486
00:36:11,124 --> 00:36:12,834
- Please excuse me. Okay?
- You're leaving?

487
00:36:12,918 --> 00:36:15,170
Yes, I'll leave
after saying goodbye to Mr. Lee.

488
00:36:15,253 --> 00:36:16,713
- Eat up, then.
- Thanks.

489
00:36:16,797 --> 00:36:18,757
- Goodbye.
- Goodbye.

490
00:36:21,385 --> 00:36:23,387
- Hello.
- At our club today...

491
00:36:23,470 --> 00:36:25,180
I told you to learn
how to scuba dive, didn't I?

492
00:36:25,263 --> 00:36:27,933
I became acquainted
with the famous Head of Audit

493
00:36:28,016 --> 00:36:29,351
Joo In-a, and met everyone.

494
00:36:29,434 --> 00:36:31,436
I'll introduce her to you soon.

495
00:36:32,104 --> 00:36:34,147
Mr. Moo isn't too resourceful.

496
00:36:34,231 --> 00:36:36,024
There's no way
he's becoming an executive.

497
00:36:36,817 --> 00:36:38,694
But he's a good man.

498
00:36:38,777 --> 00:36:40,946
My friend, there's no use
in living as a good man.

499
00:36:43,281 --> 00:36:44,616
Anyway, one second.

500
00:36:45,450 --> 00:36:46,785
Hey, did you arrive?

501
00:36:47,202 --> 00:36:49,871
Yes, okay. Come to the car. Okay.

502
00:36:50,205 --> 00:36:53,125
- Sorry, my chauffeur's here.
- Okay. Bye.

503
00:36:55,210 --> 00:37:00,257
Jeez. It was awful to listen to him
badmouth people for hours.

504
00:37:03,176 --> 00:37:04,803
Wait. That's...

505
00:37:05,470 --> 00:37:07,097
That's Mr. Min
from the Scuba Diving Club.

506
00:37:08,181 --> 00:37:09,558
Is he waiting for someone?

507
00:37:18,483 --> 00:37:19,609
What?

508
00:37:20,110 --> 00:37:22,779
The chauffeur service Mr. Yoon called
was actually Mr. Min?

509
00:37:23,196 --> 00:37:24,322
Not a hire?

510
00:37:25,115 --> 00:37:26,575
Goodness, that guy.

511
00:37:27,701 --> 00:37:30,412
See? I knew it the moment
he badmouthed those people.

512
00:37:31,121 --> 00:37:32,956
What an awful man.

513
00:37:36,293 --> 00:37:37,586
Mr. Noh, it's me.

514
00:37:37,669 --> 00:37:39,504
I'm calling
about Mr. Yoon of the Global Team.

515
00:37:39,588 --> 00:37:40,964
He's an awful man.

516
00:37:52,642 --> 00:37:53,769
Mr. Yoon.

517
00:37:54,728 --> 00:37:56,480
- Mr. Yoon.
- Man.

518
00:37:57,147 --> 00:37:58,899
I had too much to drink.

519
00:37:59,316 --> 00:38:00,484
One moment.

520
00:38:06,782 --> 00:38:07,991
Gosh.

521
00:38:15,999 --> 00:38:17,292
- I got it.
- Yes, sir.

522
00:38:18,251 --> 00:38:20,086
- And the key. One second.
- Right.

523
00:38:21,797 --> 00:38:23,006
You should have this hangover cure.

524
00:38:23,089 --> 00:38:25,425
Man, that's my Native Speaker.

525
00:38:25,509 --> 00:38:26,551
You're right on.

526
00:38:33,767 --> 00:38:35,685
- Native Speaker.
- Yes, sir.

527
00:38:35,769 --> 00:38:37,729
I've got your back until the very end

528
00:38:37,813 --> 00:38:39,314
so just trust and follow me.

529
00:38:39,397 --> 00:38:42,108
You know I'm the only one who
looks after you in the office, right?

530
00:38:42,192 --> 00:38:43,568
Yes, of course.

531
00:38:43,944 --> 00:38:46,321
I'm always grateful for you.

532
00:38:46,905 --> 00:38:48,782
- Give me. And go.
- Yes, sir.

533
00:38:51,493 --> 00:38:52,577
Mr. Yoon.

534
00:38:53,995 --> 00:38:55,038
Well...

535
00:38:55,455 --> 00:38:57,624
About the diving schedule
next Saturday.

536
00:38:58,041 --> 00:38:59,042
What?

537
00:38:59,751 --> 00:39:01,711
- You can't come?
- Well, it's my kid.

538
00:39:02,504 --> 00:39:04,881
- The kindergarten has a class...
- Hey.

539
00:39:04,965 --> 00:39:06,716
Who am I going to team up with, then?

540
00:39:06,800 --> 00:39:10,053
I was really pissed partnering up
with that punk, the club president.

541
00:39:10,136 --> 00:39:11,888
He'd stop me
from going anywhere I want to

542
00:39:11,972 --> 00:39:14,391
and ring the bell
whenever I try to grab something.

543
00:39:14,474 --> 00:39:17,686
So? Is it too big a burden
to go diving with me every week?

544
00:39:17,769 --> 00:39:18,770
Am I forcing you?

545
00:39:18,854 --> 00:39:20,438
No, Mr. Yoon. That's not the case.

546
00:39:21,147 --> 00:39:23,024
Thanks to you,
I get to enjoy a wonderful hobby.

547
00:39:24,025 --> 00:39:25,193
Yes, kid.

548
00:39:25,986 --> 00:39:27,612
So just follow my footsteps, okay?

549
00:39:27,863 --> 00:39:30,407
You need to get promoted to manager
this time, don't you?

550
00:39:30,490 --> 00:39:32,450
You're the last one
among your recruitment peers.

551
00:39:33,410 --> 00:39:34,786
Yes, you're right.

552
00:39:35,620 --> 00:39:36,913
I'll try even harder.

553
00:39:36,997 --> 00:39:39,416
Don't just try hard, you punk.

554
00:39:40,208 --> 00:39:41,751
Do it well.

555
00:39:43,378 --> 00:39:45,171
Yes, sir. I'll do it well.

556
00:39:45,255 --> 00:39:46,882
Good, Native Speaker.

557
00:39:47,465 --> 00:39:49,175
- Go, now.
- Yes. Goodnight, sir.

558
00:39:49,259 --> 00:39:50,260
Yeah.

559
00:40:03,607 --> 00:40:04,816
Mr. Min.

560
00:40:14,117 --> 00:40:16,703
I heard Mr. Yoon calling you
"Native Speaker."

561
00:40:17,162 --> 00:40:18,496
What does he mean by that?

562
00:40:18,580 --> 00:40:21,791
Everyone in my team has been abroad
except for me.

563
00:40:22,292 --> 00:40:24,044
So they say
I'm the native Korean speaker

564
00:40:24,419 --> 00:40:25,795
and nicknamed me Native Speaker.

565
00:40:29,341 --> 00:40:31,593
It doesn't sound like
a pleasant nickname.

566
00:40:31,968 --> 00:40:34,346
Mr. Min, we saw it all.

567
00:40:34,679 --> 00:40:36,681
We saw you acting
as Mr. Yoon's designated driver.

568
00:40:37,390 --> 00:40:39,935
And you don't like scuba diving

569
00:40:40,143 --> 00:40:41,603
yet you continue doing it
to serve him.

570
00:40:41,686 --> 00:40:43,647
It's just office politics.

571
00:40:44,064 --> 00:40:45,607
Everyone does this.

572
00:40:45,690 --> 00:40:46,858
No, Mr. Min.

573
00:40:47,400 --> 00:40:49,486
That's considered
workplace harassment.

574
00:40:50,362 --> 00:40:51,446
She's right.

575
00:40:51,780 --> 00:40:54,449
You should use this chance
to speak up honestly.

576
00:40:55,325 --> 00:40:57,202
- Even to your wife.
- To my wife?

577
00:40:58,620 --> 00:41:00,538
No, that is something I cannot do.

578
00:41:00,622 --> 00:41:03,541
Your wife took this the wrong way
and thinks you're having an affair.

579
00:41:03,625 --> 00:41:05,377
I'd rather live
with the misunderstanding.

580
00:41:05,460 --> 00:41:06,461
Sorry?

581
00:41:07,587 --> 00:41:09,756
I don't want my wife to find out

582
00:41:12,008 --> 00:41:13,927
that this is
how I'm being treated at work.

583
00:41:14,970 --> 00:41:16,221
Right...

584
00:41:26,356 --> 00:41:27,399
I don't think

585
00:41:28,274 --> 00:41:30,443
this is a matter we can let slide.

586
00:41:30,527 --> 00:41:32,445
This isn't just a power dynamic.

587
00:41:32,529 --> 00:41:33,947
It's gaslighting.

588
00:41:34,030 --> 00:41:36,741
I can also understand why
he doesn't want his family to know.

589
00:41:36,825 --> 00:41:39,202
Let's just tell his wife
that we confirmed that

590
00:41:39,285 --> 00:41:40,328
he isn't having an affair.

591
00:41:41,079 --> 00:41:42,080
Okay.

592
00:41:42,163 --> 00:41:44,082
Also, it looks like Mr. Min

593
00:41:44,165 --> 00:41:46,501
needs to be separated
from Mr. Yoon as soon as possible.

594
00:41:47,210 --> 00:41:48,962
I'll try to think of a way.

595
00:41:51,464 --> 00:41:54,718
This isn't something
he can handle personally.

596
00:41:56,011 --> 00:41:58,430
There must be something
that the company can do.

597
00:42:11,276 --> 00:42:13,486
VNow, we're home.

598
00:42:14,279 --> 00:42:15,822
Time to stop thinking today.

599
00:42:15,905 --> 00:42:17,282
Go home and get some rest.

600
00:42:17,490 --> 00:42:19,242
You must be tired
after diving early in the morning.

601
00:42:20,952 --> 00:42:22,037
Mr. Noh.

602
00:42:24,122 --> 00:42:25,415
Do you want to stay for ramyeon?

603
00:42:48,313 --> 00:42:49,647
That's three minutes.

604
00:42:50,690 --> 00:42:53,151
Now, take a break
and have some ramyeon.

605
00:42:54,277 --> 00:42:55,403
Hey, wait.

606
00:42:55,487 --> 00:42:58,740
Since when did the phrase,
"Do you want to stay for ramyeon?"

607
00:42:59,199 --> 00:43:02,285
come to mean, "Why don't you
eat ramyeon and work all night?"

608
00:43:02,368 --> 00:43:04,788
The meaning has changed a while ago.
You didn't know?

609
00:43:06,498 --> 00:43:08,041
Now, eat up.

610
00:43:09,793 --> 00:43:12,670
And this isn't even actually boiled.
It's cup ramyeon.

611
00:43:13,213 --> 00:43:14,881
With no kimchi or pickled radish?

612
00:43:14,964 --> 00:43:17,842
Hey, you picked out good ones
in a short amount of time.

613
00:43:18,176 --> 00:43:20,220
But this definition
is a bit too abstract.

614
00:43:20,303 --> 00:43:22,639
You should specify
the actual relevant laws here.

615
00:43:22,931 --> 00:43:25,975
It'll be more effective
to present these examples verbally.

616
00:43:26,059 --> 00:43:27,519
Can you add images
and make it more visual?

617
00:43:31,731 --> 00:43:33,817
Give me some time to eat ramyeon.

618
00:43:33,900 --> 00:43:35,568
Isn't this example too much?

619
00:43:35,652 --> 00:43:37,487
Is there anything more universal?

620
00:43:40,907 --> 00:43:43,785
- What? Which one?
- This one.

621
00:43:44,410 --> 00:43:47,413
Workplace harassment
always starts quietly.

622
00:43:47,872 --> 00:43:51,793
It begins with a good morning
and an exchange of a glance.

623
00:43:52,669 --> 00:43:54,629
Then you slowly
become excluded from the team

624
00:43:54,712 --> 00:43:56,798
or get forced to do
an unreasonable amount of overtime.

625
00:43:57,257 --> 00:43:59,134
Sometimes the perpetrator goes,
"You can handle that."

626
00:43:59,217 --> 00:44:01,177
But other times, they go,
"Why do you do things your way?"

627
00:44:01,261 --> 00:44:02,512
"Do you think work is a joke?"

628
00:44:05,140 --> 00:44:06,641
What's truly scary is this.

629
00:44:06,724 --> 00:44:08,184
As these instances continue

630
00:44:08,268 --> 00:44:10,645
the victim begins
to blame themselves.

631
00:44:11,062 --> 00:44:12,564
"Am I the weird one?"

632
00:44:12,814 --> 00:44:14,107
"Am I too sensitive?"

633
00:44:14,190 --> 00:44:15,358
"Do people hate me?"

634
00:44:15,441 --> 00:44:16,776
THE VICTIM'S PSYCHOLOGICAL CHANGES

635
00:44:16,860 --> 00:44:19,904
This kind of anxiety makes the victim
accept such absurd requests.

636
00:44:24,033 --> 00:44:25,118
Everyone.

637
00:44:25,827 --> 00:44:28,163
The absurd one
is always the perpetrator.

638
00:44:28,580 --> 00:44:30,415
Do not doubt yourself or hesitate.

639
00:44:30,498 --> 00:44:32,417
Also, do not hide but report it.

640
00:44:34,085 --> 00:44:36,337
The company is obligated
to guard and protect

641
00:44:36,421 --> 00:44:38,381
the valued human resources
of its workplace.

642
00:44:40,175 --> 00:44:41,301
Do you understand?

643
00:44:41,384 --> 00:44:42,510
- Yes.
- Yes.

644
00:44:47,098 --> 00:44:48,600
Excuse me, Mr. Noh.

645
00:44:50,435 --> 00:44:52,395
- Hello, Mr. Min.
- Hello.

646
00:44:53,521 --> 00:44:56,316
Actually, I got the chance
to go to the US as an expatriate.

647
00:44:57,734 --> 00:44:58,735
Congratulations.

648
00:44:59,611 --> 00:45:02,238
I heard the opportunity
was originally meant for you.

649
00:45:02,322 --> 00:45:03,948
I hope you didn't have to step back
because of me.

650
00:45:04,032 --> 00:45:06,201
That's not something
I can just give up to someone.

651
00:45:06,618 --> 00:45:09,162
You're going because you are
more than qualified for the job.

652
00:45:10,288 --> 00:45:11,539
Thank you.

653
00:45:11,623 --> 00:45:14,751
Also, I saw that
Mr. Yoon got disciplined.

654
00:45:15,168 --> 00:45:17,045
- Is it because of me?
- Oh, no.

655
00:45:17,503 --> 00:45:19,214
We confirmed an instance of him

656
00:45:19,297 --> 00:45:21,966
leaving his workplace
during a business trip to go diving.

657
00:45:22,342 --> 00:45:25,011
That's why he got disciplined.
So don't worry about it.

658
00:45:25,094 --> 00:45:26,804
I see. Is that right?

659
00:45:28,139 --> 00:45:29,515
Have fun while you work abroad.

660
00:45:29,599 --> 00:45:31,643
I hope you go there
and get revitalized.

661
00:45:31,726 --> 00:45:32,769
I will.

662
00:45:33,311 --> 00:45:34,771
My wife is thrilled.

663
00:45:36,105 --> 00:45:37,315
I'll have a good time.

664
00:45:39,484 --> 00:45:40,526
Also

665
00:45:41,236 --> 00:45:42,362
you two look great together.

666
00:45:43,279 --> 00:45:45,073
- Sorry?
- Well...

667
00:45:56,668 --> 00:45:58,753
You can notice lots of things
when you're underwater.

668
00:46:00,255 --> 00:46:01,589
Even as you were diving with me

669
00:46:01,673 --> 00:46:03,258
your attention and mind

670
00:46:03,508 --> 00:46:05,301
were all on Ms. Joo over there.

671
00:46:06,302 --> 00:46:08,805
You kept my secret

672
00:46:09,305 --> 00:46:10,848
so I will keep yours, too.

673
00:46:11,432 --> 00:46:12,600
Don't worry.

674
00:46:12,934 --> 00:46:14,435
- Thank you.
- Sure.

675
00:46:19,023 --> 00:46:20,483
Nice shot!

676
00:46:22,110 --> 00:46:24,404
- You're ready to go out and play.
- Thank you, sir.

677
00:46:24,570 --> 00:46:27,615
I think I can play even better,
thanks to your lessons.

678
00:46:28,408 --> 00:46:29,742
Yes, right.

679
00:46:29,826 --> 00:46:31,828
I looked up the case
on Haemu Pharmaceutical

680
00:46:31,911 --> 00:46:33,538
and I did not get anything
during the handover.

681
00:46:33,830 --> 00:46:37,667
Really? Despite all those many audits

682
00:46:38,334 --> 00:46:39,752
there are no documents left behind?

683
00:46:40,169 --> 00:46:42,630
Yes. By any chance,
are you more concerned

684
00:46:42,839 --> 00:46:46,301
because Vice President Jeon Jae-yeol
was the previous president there?

685
00:46:48,344 --> 00:46:49,512
I don't know.

686
00:46:53,474 --> 00:46:55,435
Nice shot!
It's going straight to the pin!

687
00:46:55,852 --> 00:46:57,979
You got it right next to the hole.

688
00:46:58,479 --> 00:46:59,522
Gosh.

689
00:46:59,605 --> 00:47:01,357
Man, I already said
I came to play golf.

690
00:47:04,068 --> 00:47:05,194
Hey, what's up?

691
00:47:07,947 --> 00:47:09,073
Really?

692
00:47:09,741 --> 00:47:11,367
My sister-in-law is back?

693
00:47:41,147 --> 00:47:42,732
Is it because it's been a while?

694
00:47:43,316 --> 00:47:44,984
You look kind of pretty
when you sleep.

695
00:47:45,777 --> 00:47:47,111
I heard you got sick.

696
00:47:47,779 --> 00:47:49,447
Acute alcohol intoxication?

697
00:47:50,323 --> 00:47:52,575
Didn't you tell me
to get my addiction treated?

698
00:47:52,658 --> 00:47:55,036
This is freaking hilarious.

699
00:47:57,205 --> 00:47:58,247
When did you return?

700
00:47:58,331 --> 00:48:00,124
Dad gave me a hard time

701
00:48:00,208 --> 00:48:02,794
about being abroad
while you were in this mess.

702
00:48:04,087 --> 00:48:05,338
Anyway, what happened?

703
00:48:07,382 --> 00:48:09,884
I'm sure it wasn't because
you missed me so much.

704
00:48:11,761 --> 00:48:13,179
Were you that pissed

705
00:48:13,262 --> 00:48:15,056
about your brother becoming
co-vice president?

706
00:48:15,556 --> 00:48:17,058
Are you serious?

707
00:48:20,937 --> 00:48:23,231
What is this? You're boring.

708
00:48:23,648 --> 00:48:24,649
Hyun-young.

709
00:48:26,359 --> 00:48:27,402
Yes?

710
00:48:28,403 --> 00:48:29,529
Let's call it quits.

711
00:48:29,904 --> 00:48:30,905
What?

712
00:48:36,369 --> 00:48:37,453
Let's get divorced.

713
00:48:37,995 --> 00:48:39,497
What is this nonsense?

714
00:48:40,456 --> 00:48:42,041
Why should we get divorced?

715
00:48:42,125 --> 00:48:43,626
You're unhappy with me too.

716
00:48:45,795 --> 00:48:47,213
It's time to free each other.

717
00:48:49,590 --> 00:48:51,008
Let me know when you've decided.

718
00:48:52,510 --> 00:48:54,554
We can discuss the rest
through our lawyers.

719
00:48:59,392 --> 00:49:01,686
Hey, you have to tell me the reason.

720
00:49:02,061 --> 00:49:04,730
You and I didn't get married
to be happy, anyway.

721
00:49:05,481 --> 00:49:07,191
Why are you suddenly doing this?

722
00:49:07,442 --> 00:49:09,193
Have you finally lost it
just like your mom?

723
00:49:12,196 --> 00:49:14,073
I no longer want to live like this.

724
00:49:16,659 --> 00:49:17,743
You know you have

725
00:49:19,954 --> 00:49:22,498
zero chance at becoming the successor
if you divorce me, right?

726
00:49:25,251 --> 00:49:26,377
Hyun-young.

727
00:49:28,379 --> 00:49:30,006
I'll manage my own life.

728
00:49:31,090 --> 00:49:32,383
So please

729
00:49:33,551 --> 00:49:34,927
just divorce me.

730
00:49:51,611 --> 00:49:54,238
Hey, my husband is acting weird.

731
00:49:56,407 --> 00:49:57,700
Can you do some digging?

732
00:50:05,541 --> 00:50:08,169
When do you get off work?
Come to my place for dinner.

733
00:50:08,252 --> 00:50:09,295
JOO IN-A

734
00:50:09,378 --> 00:50:11,714
Why? Are you telling me
to stop by for ramyeon again?

735
00:50:18,638 --> 00:50:20,723
Today is the real deal.

736
00:50:27,021 --> 00:50:29,273
Great work today, everyone.

737
00:50:29,690 --> 00:50:30,983
- Great work today.
- Great work today.

738
00:50:34,195 --> 00:50:35,446
What was that?

739
00:50:35,530 --> 00:50:36,948
I think Ms. Joo just winked at me.

740
00:50:37,031 --> 00:50:39,158
- What?
- You must've seen something weird.

741
00:50:39,242 --> 00:50:42,036
Or she must've squinted
because she had something in her eye.

742
00:50:42,119 --> 00:50:44,038
No, I'm serious.

743
00:50:46,123 --> 00:50:48,042
- She did this.
- Do you think

744
00:50:48,543 --> 00:50:50,086
this is a sign of some sort?

745
00:50:50,169 --> 00:50:53,047
For what? Like, "You are sealed
for overtime tomorrow"?

746
00:50:53,130 --> 00:50:55,007
Her eyes must've stung.

747
00:50:55,091 --> 00:50:57,134
Stop talking nonsense. All right.

748
00:50:57,635 --> 00:50:59,595
We never got a chance to have

749
00:50:59,679 --> 00:51:01,597
a proper team dinner
after Mr. Noh got discharged.

750
00:51:02,056 --> 00:51:04,267
Why don't we go out
and eat something delicious?

751
00:51:04,350 --> 00:51:05,768
- Okay.
- I'd love to.

752
00:51:05,851 --> 00:51:07,520
Ms. Yoon?

753
00:51:07,603 --> 00:51:09,855
Well, it depends on what we eat.

754
00:51:09,939 --> 00:51:12,275
Oh, my.
I can't believe she's saying that.

755
00:51:13,693 --> 00:51:15,987
We need to eat
something really good today, then.

756
00:51:16,320 --> 00:51:18,823
It's been a while, so I'll let us use
the corporate card!

757
00:51:19,198 --> 00:51:21,200
- All right!
- Are we unleashing the company card?

758
00:51:21,284 --> 00:51:22,577
That means we have to go.

759
00:51:22,660 --> 00:51:23,828
- Let's go.
- Wait.

760
00:51:26,205 --> 00:51:27,707
I'm so sorry, but today...

761
00:51:29,584 --> 00:51:32,211
I really want to go, too.

762
00:51:35,131 --> 00:51:36,966
But I have an important appointment.

763
00:51:39,051 --> 00:51:40,386
I see.

764
00:51:41,971 --> 00:51:43,931
It's okay. We can work overtime.

765
00:51:44,015 --> 00:51:45,516
- Yes.
- Me too.

766
00:51:48,227 --> 00:51:50,438
- Overtime it is, then.
- It is.

767
00:51:57,403 --> 00:51:58,821
Let's see.

768
00:52:07,455 --> 00:52:10,499
Oh, my. What brings you
to the 14th floor, Ms. Park?

769
00:52:11,250 --> 00:52:13,169
I had to deliver something
to the Planning Team.

770
00:52:13,252 --> 00:52:14,629
Is that so?

771
00:52:29,685 --> 00:52:31,312
You must be enjoying yourself...

772
00:52:35,358 --> 00:52:36,651
caught between two men.

773
00:52:41,530 --> 00:52:42,865
Among the two men

774
00:52:43,199 --> 00:52:45,117
exactly which one
are you furious about?

775
00:52:45,368 --> 00:52:48,412
If I tell you,
will you let me have one of them?

776
00:52:49,538 --> 00:52:52,416
In that case,
it doesn't have to be Ki-jun.

777
00:52:53,084 --> 00:52:55,294
There's no need to do that.

778
00:52:56,671 --> 00:52:57,838
You two will be over shortly.

779
00:52:58,631 --> 00:53:00,883
That's how he handles
all his romantic relationships.

780
00:53:01,676 --> 00:53:02,677
Very casual.

781
00:53:07,223 --> 00:53:08,224
Let's say

782
00:53:09,558 --> 00:53:11,352
I back down from Jeon Jae-yeol.

783
00:53:12,228 --> 00:53:13,854
Can you even have him, A-jeong?

784
00:53:15,815 --> 00:53:17,692
I get that you're upset because of me

785
00:53:18,192 --> 00:53:19,485
but try not to cross the line.

786
00:53:19,944 --> 00:53:21,654
I may look quite young

787
00:53:21,737 --> 00:53:23,489
but I am an executive member
of this company.

788
00:53:24,031 --> 00:53:25,324
Executive Assistant Park A-jeong.

789
00:53:32,206 --> 00:53:33,207
Excuse me.

790
00:53:39,714 --> 00:53:42,883
- The White Blood Cell show!
- The White Blood Cell show!

791
00:53:48,431 --> 00:53:49,432
Go.

792
00:53:49,890 --> 00:53:51,350
Hey, how do you do that?

793
00:53:51,434 --> 00:53:53,102
Open up your throat

794
00:53:53,394 --> 00:53:54,645
and throw it in.

795
00:53:54,729 --> 00:53:56,814
Give me just a little bit of time.

796
00:53:57,148 --> 00:53:58,899
I'll be there soon
after I humor them.

797
00:53:58,983 --> 00:54:00,526
That's so amazing.

798
00:54:00,735 --> 00:54:04,530
- I mean, how do you do this?
- It's not a big deal.

799
00:54:05,156 --> 00:54:08,159
- You could even do an eating show.
- He could.

800
00:54:08,242 --> 00:54:10,578
Why won't the meat get cooked?
Is the heat too weak?

801
00:54:10,661 --> 00:54:12,163
No, it's the highest.

802
00:54:12,246 --> 00:54:14,707
It's taking a while
because the cut is so thick.

803
00:54:15,374 --> 00:54:17,126
Give me that. I'll do it.

804
00:54:17,209 --> 00:54:19,587
- No, I'll do it.
- It's okay. I'm on a diet, anyway.

805
00:54:19,670 --> 00:54:21,046
- I'll do it.
- No, I...

806
00:54:21,130 --> 00:54:22,465
- Give me that too.
- Goodness.

807
00:54:23,591 --> 00:54:26,093
All right! Eat your meat! Hurry!

808
00:54:26,177 --> 00:54:27,762
- All right!
- I'd love to!

809
00:54:27,845 --> 00:54:29,263
Eat up your meat!

810
00:54:29,346 --> 00:54:30,806
- I will.
- All right.

811
00:54:39,774 --> 00:54:40,858
Thanks.

812
00:54:43,235 --> 00:54:45,196
Do you not need
a toothbrush and a razor?

813
00:54:45,905 --> 00:54:48,199
- What?
- Aren't you having a hot night?

814
00:54:48,657 --> 00:54:49,867
You have to grab a toothbrush

815
00:54:50,075 --> 00:54:51,076
for your partner.

816
00:54:53,245 --> 00:54:55,080
It's been so long for me.

817
00:54:55,873 --> 00:54:57,124
Where can I find one?

818
00:54:57,541 --> 00:54:59,126
Can you drink more?

819
00:54:59,210 --> 00:55:01,962
- Yes.
- I get drunk really easily.

820
00:55:02,755 --> 00:55:05,007
- But...
- All right, everyone. Your glasses.

821
00:55:05,090 --> 00:55:06,801
Let's make a toast! Cheers!

822
00:55:06,884 --> 00:55:09,011
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

823
00:55:09,094 --> 00:55:11,639
- Drink up.
- You can take your alcohol.

824
00:55:11,722 --> 00:55:13,516
- Why don't you have another drink?
- Shall we?

825
00:55:15,017 --> 00:55:16,811
Okay. We're partying
until we drop and die tonight.

826
00:55:16,894 --> 00:55:18,020
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

827
00:55:19,313 --> 00:55:20,981
- Chug your drink!
- Yes!

828
00:55:22,942 --> 00:55:25,361
- Okay.
- Who needs a drink?

829
00:55:26,237 --> 00:55:28,072
Now, another toast!

830
00:55:29,114 --> 00:55:30,574
- Cheers.
- It's the last one.

831
00:55:30,658 --> 00:55:32,201
- The last one.
- The last one!

832
00:55:32,284 --> 00:55:35,454
- It's the last drink here!
- Hey!

833
00:55:35,538 --> 00:55:36,997
That was so good.

834
00:55:37,540 --> 00:55:39,083
Where are we going for round two?

835
00:55:39,166 --> 00:55:41,293
- A karaoke room.
- Let's go karaokeing.

836
00:55:42,670 --> 00:55:44,213
- Mr. Noh. Where's Mr. Noh?
- Yes!

837
00:55:47,466 --> 00:55:48,551
- Hey!
- Come back.

838
00:55:48,926 --> 00:55:50,886
- You can't run away.
- Get back here.

839
00:55:50,970 --> 00:55:52,304
You can't leave today.

840
00:55:52,388 --> 00:55:55,516
- Not today.
- You're the hero tonight.

841
00:55:55,599 --> 00:55:58,853
Drunk as a fish

842
00:55:58,936 --> 00:56:02,439
I am dead drunk

843
00:56:02,898 --> 00:56:06,193
I have fallen

844
00:56:06,277 --> 00:56:09,321
For the scent of your love

845
00:56:09,488 --> 00:56:10,865
I have fallen!

846
00:56:11,198 --> 00:56:14,451
Oh, oh, oh

847
00:56:14,535 --> 00:56:16,453
- All right!
- Sing it!

848
00:57:07,796 --> 00:57:08,797
My goodness.

849
00:57:16,555 --> 00:57:18,057
- Hello?
- Okay!

850
00:57:19,099 --> 00:57:20,100
I'm sorry.

851
00:57:20,351 --> 00:57:23,270
They're holding me back
like today is my last day on earth.

852
00:57:23,896 --> 00:57:25,481
I'm so sorry.

853
00:57:26,440 --> 00:57:28,776
I think it'll take
just a little longer.

854
00:57:28,859 --> 00:57:30,069
Is that so?

855
00:57:30,527 --> 00:57:31,904
Well, I can't help it.

856
00:57:32,196 --> 00:57:34,657
Team dinners are a part of work,
so make sure you stay until the end.

857
00:57:38,911 --> 00:57:40,579
At least he won't be hungry.

858
00:57:41,872 --> 00:57:44,166
That means I'll have to eat

859
00:57:44,249 --> 00:57:46,835
which means my tummy will stick out.

860
00:57:46,919 --> 00:57:48,170
But what can I do?

861
00:57:54,510 --> 00:57:55,511
What?

862
00:57:58,180 --> 00:57:59,390
He said he'd be late.

863
00:58:00,557 --> 00:58:02,309
What is this? A surprise?

864
00:58:04,311 --> 00:58:05,562
You're here already?

865
00:58:13,278 --> 00:58:15,280
- Hey! I'm feeling too great!
- No.

866
00:58:15,364 --> 00:58:17,032
- Just one more bottle.
- Oh, no.

867
00:58:17,116 --> 00:58:19,118
Drunk as a fish

868
00:58:19,201 --> 00:58:20,202
Goodbye!

869
00:58:20,285 --> 00:58:21,620
- Goodbye!
- Boys!

870
00:58:21,829 --> 00:58:23,330
- I'm feeling too great.
- Bye, now.

871
00:58:23,414 --> 00:58:24,999
Time to go!

872
00:58:25,082 --> 00:58:27,001
Come on, man. One more bottle.

873
00:58:28,127 --> 00:58:30,045
- Now.
- All right. I get it.

874
00:58:30,129 --> 00:58:31,255
Okay, then.

875
00:58:31,630 --> 00:58:33,632
Mr. Noh, let's grab
just one more drink.

876
00:58:33,716 --> 00:58:35,801
- Great. I just need one more drink.
- Awesome.

877
00:58:35,884 --> 00:58:37,177
- No.
- What?

878
00:58:37,261 --> 00:58:39,013
That's all for today.
Maybe next time, okay?

879
00:58:39,096 --> 00:58:40,597
- There is no next time.
- There's only today.

880
00:58:40,681 --> 00:58:41,765
- No.
- Where are you going?

881
00:58:41,849 --> 00:58:43,809
- Mr. Noh!
- Just one more drink!

882
00:58:44,101 --> 00:58:46,061
- Mr. Noh!
- Don't go!

883
00:58:50,649 --> 00:58:52,651
You must've been expecting someone.

884
00:58:52,735 --> 00:58:54,028
Yes, I don't know why you're here

885
00:58:54,111 --> 00:58:56,238
but I want you to keep it short
and leave.

886
00:58:58,365 --> 00:58:59,825
I may sound like an idiot

887
00:59:00,868 --> 00:59:03,162
but even as I married
someone who wasn't you

888
00:59:03,746 --> 00:59:05,873
I never once had thought
I had lost you.

889
00:59:08,333 --> 00:59:10,127
That's a selfish thought.

890
00:59:10,502 --> 00:59:12,755
You said you'd be on my side.

891
00:59:14,465 --> 00:59:16,216
I think I lived my life
depending on those words.

892
00:59:17,593 --> 00:59:18,844
You said you were
honoring your words.

893
00:59:20,471 --> 00:59:21,555
I don't care what it is.

894
00:59:25,059 --> 00:59:28,187
I'm getting a divorce.
I told my wife, too.

895
00:59:34,068 --> 00:59:35,527
What do you think you're doing?

896
00:59:36,779 --> 00:59:38,697
What kind of response
did you expect from me?

897
00:59:39,406 --> 00:59:43,410
"Wow, Jae-yeol is divorcing!
I'm going to date him now!"

898
00:59:43,619 --> 00:59:45,370
- Did you think I'd say that?
- I know

899
00:59:45,454 --> 00:59:47,414
I can't get you back
even if I get divorced.

900
00:59:48,999 --> 00:59:50,209
I know

901
00:59:51,043 --> 00:59:52,753
I've lost you for good.

902
00:59:54,671 --> 00:59:58,050
But no matter what I do,
I couldn't let my feelings go.

903
01:00:00,385 --> 01:00:02,221
The least I can do
is be honest with my feelings.

904
01:00:03,722 --> 01:00:05,057
That's why I'm divorcing.

905
01:00:06,391 --> 01:00:08,060
It's not because of you
but because of me.

906
01:00:09,645 --> 01:00:10,896
It's killing me.

907
01:00:20,114 --> 01:00:21,490
I regret everything, In-a.

908
01:00:29,414 --> 01:00:31,041
I'm sorry.
I got here too late, didn't I?

909
01:00:37,923 --> 01:00:39,383
The one
you had been waiting for is here.

910
01:00:41,552 --> 01:00:44,054
I'm done talking, so excuse me.

911
01:01:21,800 --> 01:01:23,886
Wow, you prepared a lot of things.

912
01:01:25,721 --> 01:01:27,431
Did you make the pasta yourself?

913
01:01:27,973 --> 01:01:29,766
It looks great.

914
01:01:31,435 --> 01:01:32,769
I got these delivered.

915
01:01:37,482 --> 01:01:39,443
Good call. Delivery food is the best.

916
01:01:39,693 --> 01:01:42,321
Haemu Group's Head of Audit
couldn't have had any time to cook.

917
01:01:43,405 --> 01:01:45,574
You need to use all your free time
to stare at my face.

918
01:01:46,783 --> 01:01:47,951
Aren't you going to ask?

919
01:01:50,120 --> 01:01:51,496
You're in a foul mood.

920
01:01:51,830 --> 01:01:52,956
And you must be curious.

921
01:01:53,665 --> 01:01:56,043
Stop beating around the bush
and just ask me.

922
01:02:04,009 --> 01:02:05,010
I do want to know.

923
01:02:05,844 --> 01:02:07,429
And yes, I'm in a foul mood.

924
01:02:08,764 --> 01:02:09,806
But I

925
01:02:10,474 --> 01:02:12,142
do not want to make myself ask.

926
01:02:13,435 --> 01:02:14,937
It's probably something
between you two.

927
01:02:25,239 --> 01:02:26,531
I guess today isn't a good day.

928
01:02:27,366 --> 01:02:28,825
And you prepared so much.

929
01:02:36,083 --> 01:02:38,335
Don't drink, and go to sleep early.

930
01:02:39,044 --> 01:02:40,337
You have to be at work tomorrow.

931
01:02:41,588 --> 01:02:42,589
Okay?

932
01:02:43,715 --> 01:02:44,758
I'll get going now.

933
01:03:47,654 --> 01:03:48,739
Don't go.

934
01:03:57,539 --> 01:03:58,832
Stay by my side.

935
01:06:13,258 --> 01:06:14,301
Joo In-a...

936
01:06:16,136 --> 01:06:18,680
What on earth is she to you?

937
01:06:20,265 --> 01:06:22,309
She's someone I would die with.

938
01:06:23,894 --> 01:06:26,021
Can you even give up everything
for that woman?

939
01:06:26,688 --> 01:06:27,772
If I must.

940
01:06:28,231 --> 01:06:29,941
Let's say
I back down from Jeon Jae-yeol.

941
01:06:30,942 --> 01:06:32,444
Can you even have him, A-jeong?

942
01:06:49,753 --> 01:06:51,963
My gosh. We almost ran late.

943
01:06:52,214 --> 01:06:53,840
And I'm never late to work.

944
01:06:53,924 --> 01:06:56,718
And I never wear the same tie
two days in a row.

945
01:06:57,511 --> 01:06:58,970
That's the thing about dating.

946
01:06:59,054 --> 01:07:01,556
New definitions are introduced
to your dictionary.

947
01:07:01,640 --> 01:07:03,016
You're a smooth talker.

948
01:07:03,725 --> 01:07:05,018
But I can't accept being late.

949
01:07:06,102 --> 01:07:07,687
Have another great day.

950
01:07:10,106 --> 01:07:11,816
- You too.
- Thanks.

951
01:07:19,533 --> 01:07:21,076
Good morning.

952
01:07:21,159 --> 01:07:22,786
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

953
01:07:22,869 --> 01:07:24,037
Good morning.

954
01:07:26,039 --> 01:07:27,332
SENT BY NONAME
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

955
01:07:40,679 --> 01:07:42,806
REPORTING MS. JOO IN-A

956
01:07:45,976 --> 01:07:47,727
- What?
- What is this?

957
01:07:47,811 --> 01:07:48,895
Did you see it?

958
01:07:51,856 --> 01:07:54,276
I'd like to report
on Ms. Joo In-a's private life.

959
01:07:55,986 --> 01:07:57,946
Ms. Joo In-a remains aloof

960
01:07:58,029 --> 01:08:00,448
while keeping an eye on others
and punishing them

961
01:08:01,074 --> 01:08:03,285
but she's actually a hypocrite

962
01:08:03,827 --> 01:08:05,453
who lives
a very complicated private life.

963
01:08:06,538 --> 01:08:07,581
I attach

964
01:08:08,373 --> 01:08:11,543
a picture of Ms. Joo In-a
with her superior, who is married.

965
01:09:11,394 --> 01:09:14,314
FILING FOR LOVE

966
01:09:42,425 --> 01:09:43,760
Is the rumor about Ms. Joo true?

967
01:09:43,843 --> 01:09:47,222
So who's the man in the photo
that you exchanged greetings with?

968
01:09:47,514 --> 01:09:49,766
I know he's the vice president,
this feels way out of...

969
01:09:49,849 --> 01:09:52,352
Don't frown. You'll get wrinkles.

970
01:09:52,435 --> 01:09:54,521
I'll be an iron fortress! Let's go!

971
01:09:54,604 --> 01:09:55,855
Are you crying?

972
01:09:56,064 --> 01:09:57,649
You know, Ms. Joo's mail...

973
01:09:57,732 --> 01:10:01,027
The sender's location was traced
to Mr. Noh Ki-jun's home.

974
01:10:01,111 --> 01:10:03,905
Are you going to save me
like a knight in shining armor?

975
01:10:03,988 --> 01:10:05,031
Just say I did it.

976
01:10:05,115 --> 01:10:07,200
Mr. Noh Ki-jun will face
disciplinary action.

977
01:10:08,159 --> 01:10:09,411
I'll take responsibility.

978
01:10:22,882 --> 01:10:24,884
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn
and Jennifer Lim

